multiple_choice_question.text: Figure 1 depicts two ribbon presentations. What type of equivalence relates these two presentations?
Figure 2 illustrates the three allowable moves for what type of equivalence between ribbon presentations?

choices: The quandle operation for the fundamental quandle of a link L in any space M.
Two isotopic ribbon presentations of a link L.
The action of the link group on the link quandle.
A trivial handle in a ribbon presentation.

multiple_choice_question.text: This formula represents a relation in the knot quandle presentation of a ribbon n-knot. What does this relation correspond to geometrically?  be = bb1b2...bn
choices: A base in the ribbon presentation
A handle in the ribbon presentation passing through a sequence of bases
A trivial handle in the ribbon presentation
